==English==

===Etymology===
: Probably from Latin '''[[cubare]]''' (to lie, cf. [[incubus]]); probably akin to Korean '''[[굽다]]''' (gubda: to lie on, etc.) cf. '''[[눕다]]''' (nubda: to lie on one's back, cf. [[nubile]]). [You may observe the different bodily poses from those initials, /ㄱ/ and /ㄴ/, of both Korean words.]

===Noun===
'''cub'''

#The young of the [[bear]], [[fox]], [[wolf]], [[lion]] and some other animals.
# ('''the Cubs''') The [[Cub Scouts]].
# ('''Cub''') A member of the Cub Scouts.

